        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 4 at 11:27PM CDT by NWS Dodge City KS</headline>
        <description>At 1126 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm very
near Bloom, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Bloom around 1130 PM CDT.
Kingsdown around 1140 PM CDT.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
